{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3059","heading":"Foreign Malign Influence Center","label":"3059 Foreign Malign Influence Center","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/ch44/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2022—, struck out “Response” after “Influence” in section catchline.Pub. L. 117–263, § 6307(a)(1)(A)Subsec. (a). , struck out “Response” after “Influence”.Pub. L. 117–263, § 6307(a)(1)(B)Subsecs. (e), (f). , added subsec. (e) and redesignated former subsec. (e) as (f).Pub. L. 117–263, § 6307(b)","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Reference to Foreign Malign Influence Response Center, , , provided that:Pub. L. 117–263, div. F, title LXIII, § 6307(a)(4)136 Stat. 3505Dec. 23, 2022“Any reference in law, regulation, map, document, paper, or other record of the United States to the ‘Foreign Malign Influence Response Center’ shall be deemed to be a reference to the Foreign Malign Influence Center.”"],"amendments":["Amendments2022—, struck out “Response” after “Influence” in section catchline.Pub. L. 117–263, § 6307(a)(1)(A)Subsec. (a). , struck out “Response” after “Influence”.Pub. L. 117–263, § 6307(a)(1)(B)Subsecs. (e), (f). , added subsec. (e) and redesignated former subsec. (e) as (f).Pub. L. 117–263, § 6307(b)","Reference to Foreign Malign Influence Response Center, , , provided that:Pub. L. 117–263, div. F, title LXIII, § 6307(a)(4)136 Stat. 3505Dec. 23, 2022“Any reference in law, regulation, map, document, paper, or other record of the United States to the ‘Foreign Malign Influence Response Center’ shall be deemed to be a reference to the Foreign Malign Influence Center.”"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Establishment","label":"a Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is within the Office of the Director of National Intelligence a Foreign Malign Influence Center (in this section referred to as the “Center”).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Functions and composition","label":"b Functions and composition","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"be comprised of analysts from all elements of the intelligence community, including elements with diplomatic and law enforcement functions;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"have access to all intelligence and other reporting possessed or acquired by the United States Government pertaining to foreign malign influence;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"serve as the primary organization in the United States Government for analyzing and integrating all intelligence possessed or acquired by the United States Government pertaining to foreign malign influence; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide to employees and officers of the Federal Government in policy-making positions and Congress comprehensive assessments, and indications and warnings, of foreign malign influence.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Director","label":"c Director","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Appointment","label":"1 Appointment","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is a Director of the Center, who shall be the head of the Center, and who shall be appointed by the Director of National Intelligence.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Role","label":"2 Role","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"report directly to the Director of National Intelligence;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"carry out the functions under subsection (b); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"at the request of the President or the Director of National Intelligence, develop and provide recommendations for potential responses by the United States to foreign malign influence.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Annual reports","label":"d Annual reports","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In addition to the matters submitted pursuant to subsection (b)(4), at the direction of the Director of National Intelligence, but not less than once each year, the Director of the Center shall submit to the congressional intelligence committees, the Committee on Foreign Affairs of the House of Representatives, and the Committee on Foreign Relations of the Senate a report on foreign malign influence.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Matters included","label":"2 Matters included","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fd%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The most significant activities of the Center.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fd%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any recommendations the Director determines necessary for legislative or other actions to improve the ability of the Center to carry out its functions, including recommendations regarding the protection of privacy and civil liberties.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Termination","label":"e Termination","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fe%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"have the capabilities to perform the functions of the Center; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fe%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"will exercise the functions of the Center upon the termination of the Center; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fe%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the actions the Director of National Intelligence will take to conduct an orderly wind-down of the activities of the Center; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Fe%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the proposed timeline for such actions.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Definitions","label":"f Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Covered foreign country","label":"1 Covered foreign country","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Russian Federation.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Islamic Republic of Iran.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Democratic People’s Republic of Korea.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The People’s Republic of China.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F1%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any other foreign country that the Director of the Center determines appropriate for purposes of this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Foreign malign influence","label":"2 Foreign malign influence","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the political, military, economic, or other policies or activities of the United States Government or State or local governments, including any election within the United States; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3059/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3059%2Ff%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the public opinion within the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
